Feiber, Respondent, v. Lester et al., Appellants. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. July 9, 1889.) Appeal from special term, New York county.

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and Daniels and Brady, JJ.

*948B. C. Chetwood, for appellants. Goldfogle & Cohn, for respondent. Brady, J.

The questions presented on this appeal are the same as those considered in Feiber v. Smith, ante, 446, (decided herewith,) and must meet the same fate as pronounced in that case. Judgment affirmed, with costs. All concur.
